Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry all produce.

Trim, peel, and cut @carrots{9%ounce} and @parsnip{1}(trimmed and peeled) on a diagonal
into ½-inch-thick pieces. Dice @Yukon Gold potatoes{12%ounce} into ½-inch pieces. Halve,
peel, and mince @shallot{1} until you have 2 TBSP (4 TBSP for 4 servings). Pick
@parsley{¼%ounce}(leaves picked from stems and finely chopped).

Toss carrots and parsnip on a #baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of @olive oil{2%teaspoon}
and a pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Roast on top rack until golden brown and tender, ~{20-25%minutes}.

While veggies roast, place potatoes in a #medium pot{} with enough salted water to cover
by 2 inches. Bring to a boil and cook until tender, ~{15-20%minutes}.

Drain and return potatoes to pot. Mash with @butter{1%tbsp} until smooth and creamy,
adding splashes of @milk{6.75%ounce} as needed.

Stir in @Parmesan cheese{¼%cup}. Season with salt and pepper. Cover to keep warm.

While potatoes cook, melt @butter{2%tbsp} in a medium, preferably #nonstick pan{},
over medium-high heat. Cook, stirring frequently, until butter is foamy and flecked
with amber brown bits, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Turn off heat and carefully transfer to a large #bowl{}. Wipe out pan.

Pat @beef tenderloin filets{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{} and season all over with
salt and pepper.

Heat a drizzle of @vegetable oil{1%teaspoon} in pan used for butter over medium-high
heat. Add beef and cook to desired doneness, ~{4-7%minutes} per side.

Turn off heat; transfer beef to a #plate{} to rest. Wash out pan.

Melt @butter{1%tbsp} in same pan over medium-low heat. Add shallot; cook until softened,
~{1%minute}.

Stir in @beef demi-glace{1}, @water{¼%cup}, and any resting juices from beef. Simmer
until thickened, ~{2-3%minutes}. Turn off heat. Stir in @butter{1%tbsp}; season with
salt and pepper.

Add carrots, parsnip, and half the chopped parsley to bowl with brown butter; toss until
thoroughly coated.

Divide veggies, potatoes, and beef between plates. Top beef with pan sauce and remaining
chopped parsley. Serve.

